WorkItem.Description:
When you begin editing a node (after editing another different node), the focus jumps to the node that was previously edited.

To reproduce:

1, Run SimpleEditSample
2. Select element11 and hit F2 to edit
3. Hit Escape to stop editing
4. Select element12 and hit F2 to edit; *** notice focus jumps to element11 ***

I think the problem can fixed by adding 1 line to end of IsEditingManager::StopEditing()

        internal void StopEditing()
        {
            if (editedItem == null) return;

            Keyboard.Focus(editedItem);
            editedItem.IsEditing = false;
            FocusHelper.Focus(editedItem);
            editedItem = null; // <--- add this line to prevent focus jumping
        }
